1. Danas sam upoznao *studenta* iz Nemačke. (*studenta* - accusative singular, "Today I met a *student* from Germany.")
2. Na fakultetu ima mnogo *studenata*. (*studenata* - genitive plural, "There are many *students* at the faculty.")
3. *Studenti* će se sutra okupiti u amfiteatru. (*Studenti* - nominative plural, "The *students* will gather in the amphitheater tomorrow.")
4. Želja mi je da postanem *student*. (*student* - nominative singular, "My wish is to become a *student*.")
5. Na putu do fakulteta, *studentkinja* je upoznala svog budućeg muža. (*studentkinja* - nominative singular feminine, "On the way to the faculty, the *female student* met her future husband.")
6. Većina *studenata* voli da izlazi uveče. (*studenata* - nominative plural, "Most *students* like to go out at night.")
7. *Studentice* su organizovale humanitarnu akciju za decu bez roditelja. (*Studentice* - nominative plural feminine, "The *female students* organized a humanitarian action for children without parents.")
8. Kada postanem *student*, želim da studiram medicinu. (*student* - nominative singular, "When I become a *student*, I want to study medicine.")
9. Bio sam *student* pre deset godina. (*student* - nominative singular, "I was a *student* ten years ago.")
10. Na fakultetu se organizuje besplatna pomoć za *studente*. (*studente* - accusative plural, "Free help is organized for *students* at the faculty.")